knowledgeBase.title: Appointment Policies
knowledgeBase.content:
# Appointment Policies

## Cancellation Policy
Appointments must be cancelled at least 24 hours in advance to avoid a cancellation fee.

## Late Arrival Policy
If you arrive more than 15 minutes late, we may need to reschedule your appointment.

## Rescheduling
Appointments can be rescheduled up to 2 times without penalty.

knowledgeBase.title: appointment-types
knowledgeBase.content:
# Types of Appointments

## Standard Appointment (30 minutes)
Our standard appointment is suitable for routine consultations and check-ins.

## Extended Appointment (60 minutes)
Extended appointments are recommended for complex issues or initial consultations.

## Emergency Appointment (15 minutes)
Emergency slots are reserved each day for urgent matters that cannot wait for a regular appointment.

## Virtual Appointment
All appointment types can be conducted virtually via our secure video conferencing system.

knowledgeBase.title: faq
knowledgeBase.content:
# Frequently Asked Questions

## How do I reschedule my appointment?
You can reschedule your appointment by calling our office or using the online portal at least 24 hours before your scheduled time.

## What happens if I miss my appointment?
Missed appointments without prior notice may incur a fee and will require rescheduling.

## Can I request a specific consultant?
Yes, you can request a specific consultant when booking your appointment, subject to their availability.

## How early should I arrive for my appointment?
Please arrive 10 minutes before your scheduled appointment time to complete any necessary paperwork.

## What payment methods do you accept?
We accept all major credit cards, cash, and insurance for covered services.

Holiday closures will be announced at least two weeks in advance.

knowledgeBase.title: Virtual Appointment Guide
knowledgeBase.content:
# Preparing for Your Virtual Appointment

## Technical Requirements
- A device with a camera and microphone (smartphone, tablet, or computer)
- Stable internet connection
- Our secure meeting application (download link provided in confirmation email)

## Before Your Appointment
1. Test your device and internet connection
2. Find a quiet, private space
3. Have any relevant documents ready
4. Log in 5 minutes early to test your connection

## During Your Appointment
- Ensure good lighting so the consultant can see you clearly
- Speak clearly and at a normal volume
- If disconnected, try rejoining or wait for our call
